Creating DF

isro_budget <- data.frame(Year = 1999:2020,
                           Initial_Budget = c(1766,2019,2030,2263,2368,2731,3148,3610,3859,4074,4959,
                                              5778,6626,6715,6792,7238,7388,7509,9094,10783,12473,13479),
                           
                          Revised_Budget = c(1726,1909,1909,2164,2274,2540,2675,2997,3290,3499,4167,
                                              4880,4432,4880,5172,5826,6959,8045,9155,11200,12473,13479),
                          
                          GDP_growth = c(8.85, 3.84, 4.82, 3.80, 7.86, 7.92, 7.92, 8.06, 7.66, 3.09, 7.86, 8.50, 5.24, 5.46, 6.39, 7.41, 8.00, 8.26, 7.04, 6.12, 5.02, 5.02),
                           
                          Party = c("BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","Congress","Congress","Congress",
                                     "Congress","Congress","Congress","Congress","Congress","Congress",
                                     "Congress","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP")
           )

Calc. Growth figures

change_in_congress <- isro_budget %>% 
  filter(Party == "Congress") %>% 
  summarise(max(Initial_Budget) - min(Initial_Budget)) %>% pull()

change_in_congress
[1] 4061
change_in_congress_perc <- change_in_congress / pull(isro_budget %>% 
                                                    filter(Year == 2004) %>% 
                                                    select(Initial_Budget)) * 100
  
change_in_congress_perc <- round(change_in_congress_perc, 2)
change_in_congress_perc
[1] 148.7
change_in_bjp <- isro_budget %>% 
  filter(Party == "BJP", Year > 2010) %>% 
  summarise(max(Initial_Budget) - min(Initial_Budget)) %>% pull()

Initial Budget plot

Initial_budget_plot <- isro_budget %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x=Year, y=Initial_Budget, col = Party) ) +
    geom_path(aes(group = 1), arrow = arrow(type = "closed")) + 
    geom_vline(xintercept = c(2004,2014), col = c("red")) +
    
    geom_label(
          label=glue("Growth in\nISRO Budget\nin 10 years:\n \u20b9 {change_in_congress} Cr"), x=2012, y= 4500, 
          label.padding = unit(0.35, "lines"), size = 4, alpha = 0.4,
          label.size = 0.25, color = "#00bfc7",
              ) +
    geom_label(
        label=glue("Growth in\nISRO Budget\nin 6 years:\n \u20b9 {change_in_bjp} Cr"), x=2019, y= 8500, nudge_x = 0.5, 
        label.padding = unit(0.35, "lines"), size = 4, alpha = 0.4,
        label.size = 0.25, color = "#f77667", 
            ) +
  
    theme_classic() +
    labs(title = "ISRO Budget allocation wrt Political Party in Power",
         subtitle = "created by ViSa") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face="bold"),
          plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face="italic", color="maroon")) +
    ggeasy::easy_plot_title_size(size = 16) +
  
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(2)) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(2000), 
                       labels =label_dollar(prefix = "\u20b9", suffix = " Cr") )

library(directlabels)

    ggplot(aes(x=Year, y=Initial_Budget, col = Party) ) +

Gdp_growth_plot <- isro_budget %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x=Year, y=GDP_growth, col = Party) ) +
    geom_path(aes(group = 1), arrow = arrow(type = "closed")) + 
    geom_vline(xintercept = c(2004,2014), col = c("red")) +
    
    geom_text(
      label=glue("K\na\nr\ng\ni\nl\n \nW\na\nr"), x=1999, y= 5, nudge_x = .5,
      size = 4, color = "#f77667", angle = 7
          ) +
  
    geom_text(
          label=glue("Subprime Crisis"), x=2010, y= 3.3,
          size = 4, color = "#00bfc7",
              ) +
  
    geom_text(
          label=glue("Demonitization \n Reform"), x=2016, y= 7.5, 
          size = 4, color = "#f77667"
            ) +
  
    geom_text(
          label=glue("GST \n Reform"), x=2018, y= 7,
          size = 4, color = "#f77667"
            ) +

Secondary axis Plot

plot

sample plot

from: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3099219/ggplot-with-2-y-axes-on-each-side-and-different-scales

scaleFactor <- max(mtcars$cyl) / max(mtcars$hp)

ggplot(mtcars, aes(x=disp)) +
  geom_smooth(aes(y=cyl), method="loess", col="blue") +
  geom_smooth(aes(y=hp * scaleFactor), method="loess", col="red") +
  scale_y_continuous(name="cyl", sec.axis=sec_axis(~./scaleFactor, name="hp")) +
  theme(
    axis.title.y.left=element_text(color="blue"),
    axis.text.y.left=element_text(color="blue"),
    axis.title.y.right=element_text(color="red"),
    axis.text.y.right=element_text(color="red")
  )

actual plot


scaleFactor <- max(isro_budget$Initial_Budget) / max(isro_budget$GDP_growth)

isro_budget %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x=Year) ) +
    geom_col(aes(y=Initial_Budget, fill = Party), ) + 
    geom_line(aes(y = GDP_growth * scaleFactor), color = "maroon", size = 1.5) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = c(2004,2014), col = c("red")) +

    scale_x_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(2)) +
    scale_y_continuous("ISRO Budget", sec.axis = sec_axis(~./scaleFactor, name = "GDP Growth"),
                       ) +
  
    geom_label(label = "BJP in Power", size = 4, color = "#f77667", x=2001, y=13000) +
    geom_label(label = "BJP in Power", size = 4, color = "#f77667", x=2017, y=13000) +
    geom_label(label = "INC in Power", size = 4, color = "#00bfc7", x=2008, y=13000) +
    geom_text(label = "GDP gowth\nline", size = 4, color = "maroon", x=2006, y=5400) +
  
    
    theme_classic() +
    labs(title = "ISRO Budget in Bars & GDP growth line on basis of Political Party in Power",
         subtitle = "created by ViSa") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face="bold"),
          plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face="italic", color="maroon"),
          axis.title.y.right=element_text(color="maroon"),
          axis.text.y.right=element_text(color="maroon")) +
    ggeasy::easy_plot_title_size(size = 16)

Isro Budget growth

growth data

isro_budget_growth <- isro_budget %>% 
  mutate(lag_values = lag(Initial_Budget, default = 0),
         budget_growth_rate = round((Initial_Budget - lag_values) / Initial_Budget * 100, 2))

isro_budget_growth$budget_growth_rate[1] <- 0

isro_budget_growth

growth mean value

isro_budget_growth %>% filter(Party == "Congress") %>% summarise(mean(budget_growth_rate)) %>% pull()
